The paper deals with data structures for answering distance queries in planar graphs, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions techniques such as modifying graph decompositions and using the Monge property, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses tradeoffs between preprocessing time, storage space, and query time, which is a topic related to algorithm analysis and optimization (cs.SI).
